                        <br/><br/><br/><h2>文 献</h2><br><ol><br><li id="R1"><span class='au'>Gordon, S. & Taylor, P. R.</span>: <span class="ti">Monocyte and macrophage heterogeneity.</span> <span class='so'>Nat. Rev. Immunol., 5, 953-964 (2005)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16322748" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R2"><span class='au'>Wynn, T. A., Chawla, A. & Pollard, J. W.</span>: <span class="ti">Macrophage biology in development, homeostasis and disease.</span> <span class='so'>Nature, 496, 445-455 (2013)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23619691" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R3"><span class='au'>Gordon, S. & Martinez F. O.</span>: <span class="ti">Alternative activation of macrophages: mechanism and functions.</span> <span class='so'>Immunity, 32, 593-604 (2010)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20510870" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R4"><span class='au'>Duester, G.</span>: <span class="ti">Retinoic acid synthesis and signaling during early organogenesis.</span> <span class='so'>Cell, 134, 921-931 (2008)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18805086" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R5"><span class='au'>Wijffels, J. F., Hendrickx, R. J., Steenbergen, J. J. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Milky spots in the mouse omentum may play an important role in the origin of peritoneal macrophages.</span> <span class='so'>Res. Immunol., 143, 401-409 (1992)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1518954" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R6"><span class='au'>Maruya, M., Suzuki, K., Fujimoto, H. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Vitamin A-dependent transcriptional activation of the nuclear factor of activated T cell c1 (NFATc1) is critical for the development and survival of B1 cells.</span> <span class='so'>Proc. Nati. Acad. Sci. USA, 108, 722-777 (2011)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21187378" target="_blank">PubMed</a